Taraba State Governor Darius Dickson Ishaku has directed all political appointees serving in the state who are aspiring for elective positions to resign before Friday, April 8, 2022. The directive also affects political appointees serving at the local government councils including supervisory councillors, special advisers and secretaries to the LGCs. The governorâ€™s directive was contained in a statement by his Chief Press Secretary, Mr Illiya Bekyu. The governor, according to the statement, expressed appreciation to the political appointees for their contributions to the progress and development of the state.